external_knowledge:
- "sailing under the banner of their captains" refers to teams led by their designated captains;
- "vessels" metaphorically represents the teams;
- "trophies accumulated" metaphorically refers to the number of tournaments won;
- "collectively covered in terms of matches played" refers to the total number of matches played by all players in a team.

- "shining star" refers to top-performing players in terms of runs and wickets;
- "scoring and wicket-taking prowess" refers to the total runs scored and wickets taken by players;
- "grand stage of Wankhede Stadium" is a metaphor for the venue where matches are played.

- A forest analogy is used to describe teams with many players, indicating a significant number of players (more than 10).;
- The richness of a forest symbolizes the abundance and diversity of players on a team.;
- "Average runs scored" refers to the mean of runs scored by all players on a team in their matches.

sql:
SELECT team_id, matches_won
FROM team_statistics
WHERE matches_won = (SELECT MAX(matches_won) FROM team_statistics);

SELECT team_id, COUNT(match_id) AS matches_participated
FROM player_matches
GROUP BY team_id;
